Very local crowd, reminded me of a diner in Ireland. Lot's of pictures on the wall from family and friends of the owner. The food was very bad, but this is to be expected at a diner. However, this food was worse than food we've had other diners in the area; my wife was very noticeably sick for hours after. We will not go back. They do use actual eggs for the omelette, which is a plus, but there were tons of cracked egg shells in my omelette! I would have preferred that they not use actual eggs at that point because my omelette was so crunchy and gross! The homefries were burnt, my wife's sandwich was not put together very well, rendering it difficult to eat. The lunch meat was worse quality than Subway. We ended up taking most of it to go and then deciding on the way home to just throw it out. I would highly recommend not going here; I think they need major updates. There are much better diners just a fifteen minute drive away.

So Starting Off This Place is small and feels like a nice family owns it. The people who work and eat here are both very nice. People draw and paint and the  restaurant hangs it on the wall. I give them 5 stars because they use pepsi not coke. Which is better in my opinion. Also the burger tasted as good as the best one i ever ate just cheaper. The cheap price is What makes this place shine. Today i think ill go back there!

Probably below average in terms of the food, but the prices are very affordable and the staff is nice. I usually come here before getting a hair cut next door at Salvi's and there is usually a table open. They only have about 3 bench tables and about 5 counter top spots to eat but I've never seen it full. I get the breakfast sandwich, which I consider a slightly below average. The eggs are cooked appropriately but the bagel and bacon are very basic and don't taste very fresh or flavorful. Can't complain about the prices though, and it's still better food than the Dunkin Donuts across the street.
